1 287.480. 1. If an application for review is made to
2 the commission within twenty days from the date of the award
3 by any party, all parties to the case are automatically
4 retained as a party or parties to the appeal; the full
5 commission, if the first hearing was not held before the
6 full commission, shall review the evidence, or, if
7 considered advisable, as soon as practicable hear the
8 parties at issue, their representatives and witnesses and
9 shall make an award and file it in like manner as specified
10 in section 287.470. Any notice of appeal, application or
11 other paper required under this law to be filed with the
12 division or the commission shall, when mailed to or
13 transmitted by electronic facsimile meeting the requirements
14 of the division and received by the division or the
15 commission, be deemed to be filed as of the date endorsed by
16 the United States post office on the envelope or container
17 in which such paper is received, or the date received if
18 filed by facsimile. In instances where the last day for the
19 filing of any such paper falls on a Sunday or legal holiday,
20 the filing shall be deemed timely if accomplished on the
21 next day subsequent which is neither a Sunday or a legal
22 holiday. When filing by electronic facsimile meeting the
23 requirements of the division, the parties shall, on the same
24 date as the facsimile transmission, mail by the United
25 States mail the original and the requisite number of copies
26 to the commission. In addition, the commission may allow
27 filing of applications for review, briefs, motions, and
28 other requests for relief with the commission by electronic
29 means, in such manner as the commission may, by regulation,
30 prescribe.
